# NE-S Fashion Capsule Project - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview

This is a Next.js + Tailwind CSS + Framer Motion project for the NE-S fashion capsule "California Mountain Snake [SS26]". The design combines medical aesthetics with fashion storytelling, emphasizing sterile, futuristic, and emotionally restrained visuals.

## Technology Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js (App Router)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS (v4)
- **Animations**: Framer Motion
- **3D**: Spline 3D
- **Smooth Scrolling**: Lenis
- **Typography**: Geist font family (Geist Sans, Geist Mono, UnifrakturMaguntia, Spectral)

## Visual Design Principles

- **Color Palette**: White and neutral tones
- **Typography**: Geist font family with wide spacing and soft text (text-neutral-600)
- **Layout**: Surgical minimalism with negative space and central object focus
- **Header Style**: Frosted glass with light text
- **Overall Tone**: Medical aesthetics meets luxury fashion

## Animation Guidelines

- **Style**: Subtle, precise, and cinematic
- **Easing**: Use "easeInOut" or "anticipate" for smooth transitions
- **Duration**: Under 1.2s for UI fades, under 2s for scroll transitions
- **Library**: Framer Motion for all animations
- **Performance**: Keep animations GPU-friendly

## Component Architecture

- **Structure**: Modular components under `/app/components`
- **Naming**: Clear, descriptive names (e.g., `CapsuleHeader.tsx`, `ScrollIndicator.tsx`)
- **Responsiveness**: Desktop-first with simplified mobile versions
- **State Management**: React hooks for local state

## Code Standards

- **Language**: TypeScript with strict mode enabled
- **Styling**: Tailwind classes only (no inline styles or CSS files)
- **Imports**: Organized and optimized
- **Performance**: Optimize for readability and performance
- **Error Handling**: Proper error boundaries and fallbacks

